{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἐξῐσ-όω</b>, <br /> <b>make equal</b> or <b>even, bring to a level with,</b> τινί τινα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 425 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; μηδ᾽ ἐξισώσῃς τάσδε τοῖς ἐμοῖς κακοῖς[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 1507; ἐ. τοῖς μεγίστοις ἐγκλήμασι τὸ πρᾶγμα 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 4.2.1 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐ. ζυγά <b>bring</b> the teams <b>abreast,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 738 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>middle</i>, <b>make oneself equal,</b> δράκοντι μῆκος ἐξισουμένην σαύραν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Babrius Fabularum Scriptor 41.2 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, <b>to be</b> or <b>become equal,</b> with <i>dative</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.34, 6.111, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 563a, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>to be reduced to a level with,</b> τινί [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 8.13 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>to be a match for, rival,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.97, 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 2.52; πρός τινα 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Agis” 7. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>put on a level,</b> τοὺς πολίτας [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ranae” 688, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 4.91, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “de Mundo” 397a8 (_passive_). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <i>passive</i>, φύλοπις οὐκέτ᾽ ἐξισοῦται is <b>levelled, equalized,</b> i.e. <b>resolved in harmony,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 1072 (Lyric poetry); literal, ἐξισωθέντος τοῦ μέχρι τῶν τειχῶν διαστήματος \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<b>levelled,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Josephus Historicus “Bellum Judaicum” 5.3.5. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>intransitive</i>, <b>to be equal</b> or <b>like,</b> μητρὶ δ᾽ οὐδὲν ἐξισοῖ <b>acts</b> in no way <b>like</b> a mother, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 1194; ἐ. τοῖς ἄλλοις 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 6.87 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τισί <b>make</b> a line of battle <b>equal</b> to the enemy's, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 5.71. \">Refs</a>]","strongNumber":"G7336","accentedUnicode":"ἐξισόω","shortDef":"to make equal","mediumDef":"to make equal","stepGloss":"to make equal","stepTransliteration":"exisoō","count":0,"_step_Type":"verb"}]}